Description:
Renovated Unit Within Walking Distance to The Station!!
Whether you are a first home buyer, looking at downsizing or taking advantage of an investment, then this jam-packed unit is for you.
This cosy newly renovated property offers two spacious robed bedrooms, a great sized living area, brand new well-appointed kitchen with electric stove top, stainless steel oven and plenty of cupboard space, central bathroom fit with vanity & bath/shower facilities, separate toilet and laundry with external access. Fully secured private courtyard with the added extra of a small garden shed. In addition you will find a single carport and outside toilet.
Boasting freshly painted walls and brand new stunning floors boards, this unit also comes with quality blinds and reverse cycle heating and air conditioning, ensuring you'll be comfortable all year round.
Located within walking distance to Cranbourne Train station and close proximity to everything else that cranbourne has to offer: Shopping Centres, schools, restaurants and sporting/recreational facilities, this home ensures quality living meets convenience.

Description:
**UNDER OFFER / UNDER CONTRACT**
RANGEBANK ESTATE, CRANBOURNE (125367102): Surrounded by mature landscaping on a generous parcel of land, 112 Lesdon Avenue promises instant comfort with space to impress young families looking to break into the market and those looking to downsize from a larger home.
Given the amenity filled location, this home would be very easy to lease out, whilst there is also the potential for the lucky new purchaser to add some personal style and flair and, in doing so, add significant value to the property.
Behind its appealing brick facade you will find a practical floorplan offering 2 tiled living zones, including an L-shaped lounge/dining room, plus a family/meals area which adjoins the well-kept kitchen featuring an updated stainless steel oven, gas cook top and a dishwasher.
There are 3 robed bedrooms, including the master with a bay window, walk in wardrobe and a full ensuite to complement the family bathroom and second toilet. Not forgetting the ducted heating and evaporative cooling providing ample comfort and seasonal respite!
Outside you will be greeted by a double garage with remote door and roll through access to the single carport plus a covered patio, storage shed and a barbecue area. With a generous land size measuring app. 653m2 there is even gated side access for those requiring additional parking facilities!
If you believe in the age old theory that a top location equals great real estate then this is an absolute must to inspect! Sensational position within walking distance to Rangebank Primary School and Kindergarten with Lawson Pool Recreation Reserve literally across the road. Close proximity to buses, Merinda Park train station and Thompson Road, which is direct to all of the shopping facilities on offer at the Cranbourne Home Maker Centre!
With turnover in this popular estate at an all-time low don't muck around or else you will miss out!

Description:
OPPORTUNITY FOR THOSE FOCUSED ON LOCATION!
CRANBOURNE CENTRAL: A fantastic home in a central location, makes this property a very appealing proposition with unlimited potential! Set on a large block of 613m2 approx. nestled in a blue-chip location surrounded by all the town centre's local amenities, you are literally adjacent to Lurline Street shops & with Cranbourne Park Shopping centre only a brisk walk away allowing you easy access to an array of shopping outlets and cafes/restaurants.
In a secure setting with manicured gardens, the property itself makes an immediate impression from the street, whilst inside the mix of warm colours, lush outlooks and great presentation makes you feel instantly at home.
Featuring 3 spacious bedrooms, the master suite is complete with a WIR and an ensuite whilst bedrooms 2 and 3 both are in close proximity to the family bathroom with separate bath and shower facilities. A generous sized lounge room with gas heater, split system air conditioning and a ceiling fan, being the perfect spot to relax or entertain.
The central kitchen has been recently updated with ample amounts cupboard space & complete with quality appliances.
Extra accommodation is a highlight with two self-contained bungalows, including entsuite. split system air conditioning, both are separately metered for electricity & water and have council permitted, perfect for guests, the in-laws, or a growing family.
Outside extras include a fully enclosed outdoor entertaining area & double car garage/workshop.
Added features include: NBN internet which is available to both bungalows. reverse cycle heating and cooling, gas ducted heating, roller shutters to all windows, ducted vacuum with a duct outside to vacuum the car, caravan or boat & a easy-sweep floor duct in the kitchen. 5 kw 18 solar panels to save on rising electricity costs and thats just the beginning!
If you believe in the age-old theory that good real estate revolves around a central location, then you won't be disappointed!
The central area of Cranbourne is one of the most established and sought after areas. With a mix of older homes on larger blocks and units. Located within walking distance to all facilities, including the newly renovated Cranbourne Centro, a range of restaurants, Cranbourne Secondary College and Cranbourne Train Station. Cranbourne Central provides the perfect combination for any resident.

Description:
UNDER CONTRACT/ UNDER OFFER!
CRANBOURNE: This home is ripe for the taking. Perfect opportunity for all savvy investors, FHB and anyone that may be looking at downsizing.
The spacious, functional floorplan offers 3 robed bedrooms in close proximity to the updated central family bathroom with separate but adjoining toilet and 2nd sink. Upon entry you will be greeted by the spacious front lounge room providing direct access into the open plan, kitchen meals area with convenient backyard access. The updated kitchen is fitted out with a dishwasher, cooktop, electric oven and plenty of cupboard and bench space.
Added internal extras are split system air con, neutral tones throughout, a mixture of carpet, tiles & floorboards throughout. Step outside and be greeted by app. 654m2 of land. There's rear access to the great sized garage, perfect for all the toys.
If you believe in the age old theory that a top location equals great real estate then this as an absolute must to inspect! The central area of Cranbourne is one of the most established and sought after areas. With a mix of older homes on larger blocks and units. Located within walking distance to all facilities, including the newly renovated Cranbourne Centro, a range of restaurants, Cranbourne Secondary College and Cranbourne Train Station. Cranbourne Central provides the perfect combination for any resident.

Located within few minutes drive to the local shopping centres, parks, public transport, quality schools, TAFE college, community centre and all other amenities is this flat 610 square metre, titled land , ready to build with 20m wide frontage (which is something rare to get these days) would be an ideal location for you to build your next dream home. Due to the shortage of titled land in the market at the moment, this will not last for long.

Description:
Invest, Occupy or Subdivide in Central Cranbourne!
Set on a large corner block with room to move, and located close to all that Cranbourne has to offer sits this potential packed property which is sure to impress! Whether you are purchasing to live in or to invest, this home offers a lifestyle of absolute convenience and opportunity.
This stylishly updated 3 bedroom home has just been refreshed throughout offering neutral tones and stunning polished Blackbutt hardwood floors. As you enter your greeted by the generous-sized lounge room featuring large light filled windows, 3 spacious bedrooms, master bedroom with built in robes and ensuite, second & third bedrooms also with Built in robes and are serviced by the sleek central bathroom including bath and separate toilet. Fully equipped kitchen with stove top, oven and plenty of cupboard space adjoining to a family/meals area, which overlooks the enclosed back yard with paved pergola area and garden beds.
Set on a healthy 619 square metres this property could potentially be sub-divided by demolishing the existing dwelling in the future (subject to council approval) offering further opportunities.
Other features include gas wall heater, led down lights, secure double lock up garage.
With a location just moments away from all the lifestyle opportunity's, it simply doesn't get any better than this. Call today!

Description:
Nest or Invest
Immaculately presented throughout, this lovely 1 bedroom apartment is favoured with a fantastic outlook over Carlisle Park Reserve from the living area and private balcony and is located only metres from Springhill Shopping Centre, specialty shops, representing an excellent proposition for first home buyers or investors seeking high returns on their
investment.
Consisting of an inviting and bright open plan living, the apartment features a well-appointed kitchen with stainless steel appliances, gas cook top, electric wall oven, combined bathroom/ laundry with double size shower and creature comforts including split system reverse cycle air conditioner and energy efficient heat banks.
Other special features include remote lock up carport and your own private courtyard! Nothing to do here, just move in or rent out! Currently tenanted on a periodical basis at $1260 per calendar month.
Call Ola or Rebecca now for further details
** Investors: Did you know Harcourts Narre Warren South are one of the largest rental management agencies in the South East? Our department head of rentals Melanie Keating has appraised this property at $290-$295p/w ($1,260-$1,282pcm) for more details about leasing contact Melanie on 03 9705 3000 today.

Description:
Wow I want This One Darling!
If you are looking for a low maintenance home set on a 320 sqm block, then this is the one for you!
Nestled in the popular Carlisle Park Estate, overlooking an expansive park with playground, this well-presented home offers the perfect start, for first home buyer, investor or down-sizer.
Consisting of 3 carpeted bedrooms, master with own ensuite and walk in robe, remaining bedrooms with built in robes and central family bathroom. The large open plan light filled living area offers plenty of space for lounge and dining which adjoins to the well-appointed kitchen featuring gas cooking, stainless steel appliances and dishwasher. Towards the rear of the property you have access from the kitchen to the extra-large double remote control garage. The living space is further enhanced by outside where you'll find a secure, low maintenance private backyard to enjoy those pleasant evenings and fresh air. The front yard also offers very low maintenance gardens and includes an extended veranda where you can sit under and appreciate the peace and tranquillity which surrounds this home.
Other features of this home include gas ducted heating for those cool evenings and a split system air conditioner.
With the local schools, shops, transport and restaurants nearby you can enjoy the convenience of being located close to all the amenities Cranbourne has to offer.

Description:
A GOOD HOME IS NOW A GREAT HOME
Freshly renovated throughout is this easy-care 3 bedroom home located in Cranbourne Central. Whether you are looking at downsizing or wishing to get into the market as a first home buyer. This affordable home would be ideal. Nothing to do, it is without a doubt fresher than a daisy.
- Offering brand new kitchen with s/s appliances including oven/dishwasher/range hood
- New quality flooring - floating floor & tiles in wet areas
- Elegant bathroom boasting modern vanity and shower
- Master bedroom with double built in robes and other 2 with single robes
- Cosy courtyard with convenient access to the carport
Chances are, this property will not last long on the market. Terrific opportunity which you cannot afford to miss out. Best to act now, so come through our Opens or ring me for an inspection.
